Heat your #oven to 200 degrees. Scrub your @sweet potato{1.5} but leave the nutritious
skin on and chop into rough 2cm cubes. Cut the core out of the @green pepper{1}
and @red pepper{1/2} and cut the flesh into 2cm cubes. Peel the @red onion{1}
and chop into 2cm cubes.

Toss all the vegetables in @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @salt{1/2%tsp} and
@pepper{1/2%tsp}. Lay out on a #tray and cook on the top shelf for
~{20-25%minutes}.

Sandwich your @British chicken breasts{2} between 2 pieces of #cling film (if you
have some). Bash the chicken with a #rolling pin until it is 1/2cm thick all
over.

> Tip: If you don't have a rolling pin you can improvise with a heavy saucepan or
a cricket bat etc.

Rub @olive oil{1%tsp} onto the chicken breasts. Mix the @shawarma spice mix{1}
with a @salt{pinch} and rub over each of the breasts.

Heat a #large frying pan{}. Gently lay your chicken breasts in and cook on each
side for around ~{4%minutes}.

Drain and rinse the @organic lentils{1}. Toss the lentils together with the
cooked vegetables and @salt{1/4%tsp} and @pepper{1/4%tsp}.

> Tip: Use the roasting tray to toss everything together to save on washing up!

Divide your vegetables between your plates. Cut the chicken on the diagonal and
lay on top. Finally top with a little @crème fraîche{2} seasoned with a little
pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.